column11: ""DR. JEKYLL AND MR. HYDE"" Premiered In Theaters On This Day In HORROR Film HISTORY December 31st 1931!
Starring FREDRIC MARCH, MIRIAM HOPKINS & ROSE HOBART.
MakeUp By NORBERT A. MYLES & WALLY WESTMORE, Whom Both Were Uncredited. Their MakeUp For This Film Was Based On An Neanderthal Man.
Some Terror'ific Trivia About This Movie:

It Was The 1st HORROR Movie Ever To Win An Academy Award Which Went To FREDRIC MARCH, Seen Here Taking A Tea Break In Full MakeUp On Set BEHIND THE SCENES With MIRIAM HOPKINS And Director/Producer ROUBEN MAMOU
The Sound Of The Pounding Heart In The Transformation Scene Was MAMOULIAN'S Own, Recorded After He Ran Up And Down The Stairs For Two Minutes.

column11: Just off Highway 95, about halfway between Las Vegas and Reno, lies the sleepy desert town of Tonopah, where you can spend the night at THE CLOWN MOTEL ‚òÖ
Once a booming, goldmining hotspot with a population of over 50,000, Tonopah now houses just around 2,500 people.

Not only is the lobby of The Clown Hotel filled with hundreds of menacing clowns, but each and every room is clown themed as well. On each of the walls are hung portraits of famous clowns, from Bozo to Pagliac
On top of that, The Clown Motel shares a lot with a cemetery full of gold miners who died from a plague.
